3.0 DETAILED TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE

3.1 Mobility & Stabilization System

3.1.1 Hexapod Leg Architecture

```
Each Leg (6 total):
├── Hip Joint (2 DOF)
│   ├── Vertical: ±60° @ 150 Nm continuous
│   └── Horizontal: ±45° @ 120 Nm continuous
├── Knee Joint (1 DOF)
│   └── Extension: 0-120° @ 200 Nm continuous
└── Foot Assembly
    ├── Regolith Anchor: Deployable spike (0.5m penetration)
    ├── Load Sensor: 6-axis force/torque
    └── Thermal Coupling: Heated contact for frozen terrain
```

Anchoring Sequence:

1. Site Survey: Map load-bearing capacity via foot probes
2. Pre-load: Apply 50% operational force for settlement
3. Lock-out: Hydraulic locks engage, joints transition to stiff mode
4. Verification: Confirm <0.1mm movement under test load

3.1.2 Stability Requirements

· Natural Frequency: >8 Hz when anchored (avoid drilling harmonics)
· Settlement Tolerance: <5mm during 12-hour extraction cycle
· Leveling Capability: ±10° terrain compensation
· Reaction Force Absorption: 15 kN axial, 5 kN lateral during drilling

3.2 Thermal Penetration System (TPS)

3.2.1 Thermal Head Assembly

```
Thermal Head Stack:
├── Primary Heater
│   ├── Technology: Graphite resistive elements
│   ├── Temperature: 100-1200°C (adjustable)
│   ├── Power: 5-20 kW continuous
│   └── Efficiency: 85% electrical to thermal
├── Insulation Layer
│   ├── Material: Multilayer ZrO₂ aerogel
│   ├── Thickness: 50mm
│   └── Outer Temp: <100°C at 20cm from 1200°C core
├── Melt Management
│   ├── Channels: 8 radial passages
│   ├── Liner Deployment: Integrated spool system
│   └── Temperature Gradient: Controlled 0-100°C zone
└── Sensors
    ├── 8× Thermocouples (Type K, -200°C to +1350°C)
    ├── 4× Pressure (0-100 kPa absolute)
    └── 1× Optical borehole inspection camera
```

3.2.2 Penetration Modes

Mode Temperature Rate Use Case
Sublimation 200-400°C 0.05 m/hr Dry ice layers, minimizes liquid handling
Melting 1-100°C 0.1-0.3 m/hr Ice-rich zones, produces liquid water
Thermal Fracture 400-800°C 0.2-0.5 m/hr Competent ice/rock interfaces
Bake-Out 800-1200°C N/A Borehole sterilization, liner bonding

3.2.3 Thermal Control Algorithms

```
Primary Control Loop (100ms):
Input: {Desired Mode, Power Limit, Bore Stability}
Process: PID with feedforward (thermal inertia model)
Output: {Heater Power, Coolant Flow, Advancement Rate}

Constraints:
- Maximum radial thermal gradient: 50°C/cm (prevents cracking)
- Minimum liner temperature: >0°C (prevents freeze-up)
- Maximum power: 25 kW (system limit)
```

3.3 Phase Management & Extraction Column

3.3.1 Borehole Liner System

```
Liner Assembly:
Material: Kapton-Mylar-Aluminum laminate (5-layer)
Thickness: 0.5mm
Deployment: From spool in thermal head
Diameter: 30cm (deployed), 15cm (stowed)
Length: 120m capacity (4× design depth)
Sealing: Inflatable collar at 5m intervals
Thermal Rating: -180°C to +150°C
Pressure Rating: 200 kPa burst (3× operating pressure)
```

3.3.2 Phase-State Control Volume

```
Control Parameters:
├── Pressure: 0.6-50 kPa (adjustable)
├── Temperature: -10°C to +30°C (zone-dependent)
├── Vapor Fraction: 0-100% (by volume)
└── Flow Rate: 0.1-5.0 L/min

Active Systems:
├── Pressure Regulation
│   ├── CO₂ buffer gas injection
│   ├── Vacuum pump (for sublimation mode)
│   └── Relief valves (dual redundant)
├── Temperature Zones
│   ├── Heating: Resistive elements in liner
│   ├── Cooling: Heat pipes to radiators
│   └── Monitoring: 20× PT1000 sensors per 10m
└── Phase Separation
    ├── Centrifugal separator (vapor/liquid)
    ├── Flash tank (pressure reduction)
    └── Condenser (vapor to liquid)
```

3.4 Water Handling & Processing

3.4.1 Extraction Chain

```
1. CAPTURE
   ├── Method: Gravity drainage (melt) or vapor transport (sublimation)
   ├── Collection Sump: 20L capacity at base of borehole
   └── Lift System: Helical pump (0-10 L/min)

2. PRIMARY PROCESSING
   ├── Filtration: 100μm → 10μm → 1μm ceramic filters
   ├── Degassing: Vacuum flash removal of CO₂/N₂
   └── Buffer Storage: 200L insulated, pressurized (50 kPa)

3. SECONDARY PROCESSING (Conditioning)
   ├── Desalination: Reverse osmosis (if brine detected)
   ├── pH Adjustment: CO₂ stripping to neutral
   └── Sterilization: UV-C + mild chlorination (for human use)

4. STORAGE & DISTRIBUTION
   ├── Primary Tanks: 2× 1000L (insulated, heated)
   ├── Distribution: 10mm lines to base (1km max)
   └── Backup: Freeze into standardized ice blocks
```

3.4.2 Quality Specifications

Parameter Specification Standard
Particulates <10 mg/L Martian Drinking Water Standard (proposed)
Dissolved Solids <500 mg/L Electrolysis-compatible
Biological Sterile (0 CFU/100mL) Planetary protection
pH 6.5-8.5 Industrial/agricultural range
Dissolved Gases <10% saturation Prevents two-phase flow issues

3.5 Power & Thermal Systems

3.5.1 Power Architecture

```
Primary Source: Stirling Radioisotope Generator (SRG)
├── Power: 10 kWe continuous
├── Fuel: 4× GPHS (General Purpose Heat Source)
├── Mass: 180 kg
└── Lifetime: 14 years (>2 Mars cycles)

Secondary Source: Deployable Solar Array
├── Area: 20m² (stowed), 60m² (deployed)
├── Peak Output: 15 kW (Mars noon, clear)
└── Storage: 50 kWh Li-S batteries

Distribution:
400V DC Primary Bus
├── Thermal Head: 20 kW max
├── Processing: 3 kW continuous
├── Mobility: 5 kW peak
├── Computation: 0.5 kW
└── Thermal Management: 2-8 kW (season dependent)
```

3.5.2 Thermal Integration

```
Waste Heat Recovery:
SRG Reject Heat: 40 kW thermal (at 650°C)
├── 30% to borehole pre-heating
├── 40% to water tank maintenance
├── 20% to external radiator (regulated)
└── 10% to electronics thermal bus

Active Cooling:
├── Heat Pumps: COP 2.5 at ΔT=50°C
├── Radiators: 5m² emissive area (ε=0.85)
└── Phase-Change Materials: Buffer diurnal cycles
```

3.6 Computational & Autonomy Architecture

3.6.1 Processing Stack

```
Layer 1: Reflexive Control (10ms loop)
├── Processor: 2× LEON4-FT (rad-hard, lockstep)
├── OS: RTEMS Real-Time OS
└── Functions: Thermal control, pressure safety, stability

Layer 2: Tactical Operations (1s-1min loop)
├── Processor: 2× NVIDIA Jetson Orin NX (redundant)
├── OS: Linux + ROS 2
└── Functions: Extraction optimization, fault response

Layer 3: Strategic Planning (1hr-1sol loop)
├── Processor: Qualcomm QCS6490 (rad-hardened)
├── OS: QNX Neutrino
└── Functions: Site selection, production scheduling, learning
```

3.6.2 Sensor Suite

Sensor Type Quantity Function
GPR 100 MHz-1 GHz stepped frequency 1 Subsurface imaging to 50m depth
Neutron Spectrometer He-3 proportional counters 1 Hydrogen detection (water/ice)
Thermal Profiler 10m deployable probe array 1 In-situ thermal conductivity
Seismic 3-axis geophone array 4 Fracture detection, stability
Borehole Camera 5MP, LED illumination 1 Visual inspection
Water Analyzer Raman spectrometer + conductivity 1 Composition real-time
Dust Monitor Optical particle counter 2 Environmental conditions

3.6.3 Autonomy Framework

```
Subsurface Intelligence Engine:
1. PROSPECTING PHASE
   Input: Orbital data + local GPR scan
   Output: 3D probability map (water concentration)

2. DRILLING DECISION TREE
   ├── IF ice >30% by volume → Melting mode
   ├── IF ice 10-30% → Sublimation mode
   ├── IF complex layering → Adaptive hybrid
   └── IF unstable formation → Abort and relocate

3. ADAPTIVE EXTRACTION
   ├── Model-Predictive Control of thermal input
   ├── Real-time optimization of energy/water ratio
   └── Predictive maintenance scheduling

4. FLEET COORDINATION
   ├── 3+ ASWES units form "water field"
   ├── Shared subsurface model updates
   └── Coordinated production to meet demand
```

3.7 Environmental Protection

3.7.1 Dust Mitigation

· Positive Pressure: All electronics at 1.5 kPa above ambient
· Magnetic Seals: Rotating joints use ferrofluid barriers
· Electrostatic Precipitators: Air intake cleaning (99% @ 1μm)
· Self-Cleaning: Vibration + reverse pulse for radiators

3.7.2 Thermal Management

· Multi-Layer Insulation: 25-layer on critical components
· Variable Emissivity Coatings: Electrochromic outer layer
· Heat Switch Networks: Redirect heat based on needs
· Survival Heaters: RHUs (Radioisotope Heater Units) for cold survival

3.7.3 Radiation Protection

· Total Dose: 100 krad(Si) capability
· Shielding: 10mm polyethylene + 2mm tantalum local shielding
· Architecture: Triple modular redundancy + EDAC memory
· Monitor: Real-time dosimetry with safe mode triggers

