4.0 OPERATIONS & PRODUCTION

4.1 Water Extraction Process

4.1.1 Site Selection Protocol

```
Day 1-3: Regional Survey
├── GPR grid (100m spacing)
├── Neutron scan spots (10m intervals)
└── Thermal inertia mapping

Day 4: Target Identification
├── Criteria: >20% water equivalent hydrogen
├── Depth: <20m preferred
├── Stability: Low fracture probability
└── Accessibility: <5° slope, minimal boulders

Day 5: Verification Drilling
├── Pilot hole to 5m
├── Core sample analysis
└── Go/No-Go decision
```

4.1.2 Production Timeline (Typical Site)

Phase Duration Activity Water Output
Setup 1 sol Mobility to site, anchoring 0 kg
Penetration 5-20 sols Reach target depth (10-50m) 0 kg
Commissioning 1 sol Liner seal verification, system check 0 kg
Ramp-up 2 sols Gradual production increase 50-200 kg/sol
Steady-State 60-180 sols Continuous extraction 100-500 kg/sol
Decline 10 sols Production drop-off, prepare relocation 20-100 kg/sol
Decommission 2 sols Seal borehole, retract systems 0 kg

4.2 Production Metrics

4.2.1 Single Unit Performance

Metric Conservative Nominal Optimistic
Daily Production 100 kg/sol 300 kg/sol 500 kg/sol
Energy Efficiency 1.0 kWh/kg 0.7 kWh/kg 0.5 kWh/kg
Water Recovery 70% of in-situ 85% of in-situ 95% of in-situ
Availability 85% 92% 95%

4.2.2 Water Field Economics (3-unit cluster)

```
Annual Production (669 sols):
Conservative: 200,000 kg
Nominal: 600,000 kg
Optimistic: 1,000,000 kg

Mass Leverage Ratio:
Earth mass delivered: 4,200 kg (3 ASWES units)
Water produced in Year 1: 200,000-1,000,000 kg
Leverage: 48:1 to 238:1

Break-even Analysis:
Water value (Earth launch cost equivalent): $10,000/kg
Annual production value: $2M to $10M
System cost (estimate): $150M
Break-even: 7.5-15 years (terrestrial economics)
```

4.3 Integration with Martian Infrastructure

4.3.1 Direct Interfaces

```
Electrolysis Plant:
├── Supply: 100-500 kg/sol water
├── Purity: >99% H₂O
├── Pressure: 50-200 kPa
└── Temperature: 5-30°C

Agriculture Modules:
├── Supply: 10-50 kg/sol (initial)
├── Nutrients: Add injection ports
└── Sterility: UV treatment only

Industrial Cooling:
├── Closed-loop: 100-1000 kg buffer
├── Heat Rejection: 10-100 kW capacity
└── Freeze Protection: Glycol mixture options

Construction (Water-Based):
├── Concrete: 200 kg water/ton regolith aggregate
├── Soil Stabilization: 50 kg water/ton for compaction
└── Ice Construction: Direct freezing for structures
```

4.3.2 Water Distribution Network

```
Phase 1: Direct Lines (0-1km)
├── Insulated, heated pipes
├── Redundant paths
└── Automated freeze recovery

Phase 2: Grid Network (1-5km)
├── Central storage: 10,000 kg capacity
├── Pumping stations: Solar-powered
└── Quality zoning: Industrial vs. human-use lines

Phase 3: Regional System (5-20km)
├── Multiple water fields
├—— Integrated management
└—— Emergency reserves (6-month supply)
```

