6.0 RISK MITIGATION

6.1 Critical Failure Modes

Failure Mode Probability Mitigation Recovery Time
Thermal Head Burnout 5% over mission Dual elements, reduced power mode 5 sols (buddy assist)
Liner Rupture 8% per borehole Redundant layers, pressure monitoring 2 sols (patch deployment)
Borehole Collapse 12% in weak zones Real-time stability monitoring, slow advance 3-10 sols (redrilling)
Freeze-up in Lines 15% in winter Trace heating, glycol injection, pulsed flow 1-2 sols
Power System Degradation 2%/year 30% oversize, load shedding protocols N/A (graceful degradation)

6.2 Contingency Operations

Dust Storm Protocol:

```
Phase 1 (Forecast): Secure operations, retract non-essential systems
Phase 2 (Active): Enter hibernation, minimal power, sealed vents
Phase 3 (Recovery): Self-check, gradual restart (12-24 hours)
```

Low-Production Scenario:

· Switch to higher-concentration zones
· Reduce purity requirements (industrial use only)
· Implement water recycling from other processes

Multiple System Failures:

· Shed non-critical loads
· Prioritize drinking water production
· Implement buddy-system repairs
· Cannibalize units if necessary

