7.0 INTEGRATION WITH AWR-MARS ECOSYSTEM

7.1 Material Exchange

```
ASWES-Mars Outputs → AWR-Mars Inputs:
1. Water for concrete production (regolith + water = marscrete)
2. Water for dust suppression in mining operations
3. Cooling water for smelting operations
4. Hydrogen/oxygen from electrolysis for reduction processes

AWR-Mars Outputs → ASWES-Mars Inputs:
1. Structural components for water distribution
2. Replacement parts for ASWES systems
3. Power system expansions
4. Radiation shielding for surface pipes
```

7.2 Coordinated Operations

```
Example: Habitat Construction Project
Day 1-30: AWR-Mars mines regolith, produces structural elements
Day 31-45: ASWES-Mars provides water for marscrete foundations
Day 46-60: Combined system deployment (AWR places pipes, ASWES fills)
Day 61-90: Integrated pressure testing, leak check
```

7.3 Shared Autonomy Framework

· Common Communication Protocol: ROS 2 middleware
· Unified Mapping: Shared geospatial database
· Resource Negotiation: Bidding system for shared assets (power, transport)
· Learning Transfer: Water location data improves mining site selection

