APPENDICES

Appendix A: Water Phase Diagram for Mars

```
Pressure-Temperature Space:
0.6 kPa (Martian surface):
  - Ice → Vapor (sublimation) at -70°C to -10°C
  - No stable liquid phase at surface pressure

Controlled Environment (ASWES borehole):
  10-50 kPa maintained:
  - Liquid water stable at 0°C to 30°C
  - Controlled boiling at desired points
```

Appendix B: Energy Balance Calculations

```
For 1 kg water from ice at -50°C:
1. Heat from -50°C to 0°C: 105 kJ
2. Melt at 0°C: 334 kJ
3. Heat from 0°C to +5°C (extraction temp): 21 kJ
Total: 460 kJ/kg = 0.128 kWh/kg (theoretical minimum)

ASWES Efficiency:
Theoretical: 0.128 kWh/kg
Actual (system): 0.5-1.0 kWh/kg
Efficiency: 13-26% of theoretical
Losses: Borehole heating, liner conduction, pumping, processing
```

